1
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,600
Remember to take your medicine on time.

2
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,200
Okay, thank you.

3
00:01:01,439 --> 00:01:02,320
Watch your diet.

4
00:01:02,359 --> 00:01:02,799
Okay.

5
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:04,640
Professor Du,

6
00:01:04,879 --> 00:01:06,760
my master will be back soon.

7
00:01:06,959 --> 00:01:08,359
Would you like to wait?

8
00:01:08,439 --> 00:01:09,120
Okay, no problem.

9
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:09,879
I'm not in a hurry.

10
00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:11,400
I'll go back to my room.

11
00:01:21,079 --> 00:01:21,799
Sister,

12
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:24,359
you died so tragically.

13
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:26,840
Sister!

14
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:30,519
You died so tragically!

15
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:33,680
Sister!

16
00:01:34,799 --> 00:01:36,040
Lan Jianhua!

17
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:38,319
You coward, what kind of man are you?

18
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,319
Lan Jianhua, come out here!

19
00:01:40,439 --> 00:01:41,319
Lan Jianhua isn't here.

20
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,159
Who are you? What are you doing here?

21
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:44,879
What do you mean by that?

22
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:46,040
You...

23
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,680
You're Du Juan, right?

24
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,120
You look like a cuckoo,

25
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:50,519
and always intruding on others' homes.

26
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:51,079
You!

27
00:01:51,079 --> 00:01:53,120
You're old and seducing my brother-in-law.

28
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,480
What are your intentions?

29
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:55,680
You...

30
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,640
My sister,

31
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:01,319
you left too early.

32
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,920
Sister, open your eyes.

33
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,599
Look at this slut seducing your man,

34
00:02:05,719 --> 00:02:07,560
and trying to take over your clinic.

35
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:08,639
Sister,

36
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,000
may this pair of scoundrels die.

37
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,120
Get up, get up!

38
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:12,960
Let go!

39
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,319
What are you doing?

40
00:02:14,439 --> 00:02:15,520
You want to hit my sister, right?

41
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:16,560
Fine, hit her!

42
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,319
Hit her!

43
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,199
Isn't this just what you wanted?

44
00:02:19,319 --> 00:02:20,240
Come on, hit her!

45
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:21,919
Hit her!

46
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:23,960
Hit her!

47
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:25,759
What are you pretending for?

48
00:02:25,919 --> 00:02:27,120
Hit her!

49
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:28,240
Come on.

50
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:30,479
Wang Huijun,

51
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:31,560
what are you doing?

52
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:34,039
Look at her,

53
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,800
pretending so well.

54
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,639
Wang Huijun, I'm telling you,

55
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,240
if anything happens to her,

56
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:41,080
I'll call the police and see you in court.

57
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:41,719
Fine, fine.

58
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:42,120
Get lost.

59
00:02:42,199 --> 00:02:43,879
You two will meet a bad end.

60
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,319
A bad end.

61
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:45,879
Juan!

62
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:46,840
Juan!

63
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:48,159
- You will die a miserable death! - Juan!

64
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:48,759
Juan!

65
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:50,159
- Juan! - Miserable death!

66
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,400
Uncle Blue,

67
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,400
how is my mom?

68
00:03:22,199 --> 00:03:23,120
She fainted from anxiety

69
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,520
and overthinking,

70
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,639
which damaged her spleen

71
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,639
and caused qi stagnation.

72
00:03:31,719 --> 00:03:32,520
She'll be fine

73
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,039
and she'll be fine.

74
00:03:36,199 --> 00:03:36,800
Uncle Blue,

75
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:39,159
do you know about my mom's debts?

76
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:41,039
How could she owe so much?

77
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:42,919
I don't know.

78
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:44,599
She never told me.

79
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:46,919
We were supposed to

80
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,080
meet today to discuss something.

81
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:50,639
I didn't expect...

82
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:55,759
Xiao Fei,

83
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,360
I'm sorry for your mom.

84
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:58,120
No.

85
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,960
Your mother loves dignity.

86
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:02,960
But that scoundrel in the family

87
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,319
made your mother lose face.

88
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,520
Xiao Fei, don't worry.

89
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:10,319
No matter how much money your mother owes,

90
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,639
I will repay it

91
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,439
for your mother.

92
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:15,280
Uncle Blue,

93
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,519
let's not talk about this.

94
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,279
Please take care of my mother for me first.

95
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:23,959
I will

96
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,079
look into this matter.

97
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,319
Go now.

98
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:54,279
We should have sued my uncle long ago.

99
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:55,800
He's

100
00:04:56,279 --> 00:04:57,480
not mentally sound.

101
00:04:58,439 --> 00:04:59,959
Only prison can make him behave.

102
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,519
My mom has been frugal for most of her life.

103
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,920
She never spent much money.

104
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,079
How could she owe so much?

105
00:05:15,199 --> 00:05:15,920
What did you find?

106
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,000
Bank receipts.

107
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,040
All from the past few months.

108
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,920
Each transaction varies from several tens of thousands.

109
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:29,199
The beneficiary is

110
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,600
Niu Jiaojian.

111
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:33,199
Auntie has been

112
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,680
transferring money to this person.

113
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,120
Do you know him?

114
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:39,399
He doesn't sound like a relative.

115
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:42,279
I don't remember.

116
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,319
Niu Jiaojian?

117
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:48,120
Niu Jiaojian?

118
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,920
What a name!

119
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:53,199
What did you say?

120
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,279
Say it again.

121
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:57,879
Niu Jian.

122
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:58,879
What's wrong?

123
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,079
Grandpa.

124
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:05,680
Grandpa.

125
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,560
Grandpa, take a break.

126
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:10,040
I brought you some sticky rice buns.

127
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:12,959
Okay.

128
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,879
Xiao Fei,

129
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,279
put it there.

130
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:16,399
I'll eat later.

131
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,480
Du,

132
00:06:24,399 --> 00:06:26,480
you must be Little Yunfei.

133
00:06:27,839 --> 00:06:28,399
Come on.

134
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,560
Take a look.

135
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,199
This trophy

136
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:34,199
was awarded to me.

137
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:37,839
Aviation Technology Breakthrough Award.

138
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,680
Shiny?

139
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,519
Yes, as shiny as the stars.

140
00:06:41,959 --> 00:06:43,079
I'm busy.

141
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,199
Busy?

142
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:48,160
You said

143
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,040
the drawings of the fighter plane

144
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,439
have been designed for almost half a month.

145
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,399
But the arc of the wing

146
00:06:55,399 --> 00:06:56,519
is still undecided.

147
00:06:56,759 --> 00:06:57,600
How about this?

148
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,120
Let the award winner

149
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,839
give you some advice.

150
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,360
What do you mean by advice?

151
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,720
Niu,

152
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:08,839
your research is on the power system,

153
00:07:09,079 --> 00:07:10,160
which has nothing to do

154
00:07:10,319 --> 00:07:11,920
with my aerodynamic layout.

155
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:12,839
Go back

156
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,000
to your room

157
00:07:14,079 --> 00:07:15,160
and play with your trophies.

158
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:18,439
But the model you designed

159
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:21,279
adopted my correction data.

160
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,399
Don't be stubborn.

161
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,720
Grandpa.

162
00:07:25,439 --> 00:07:26,399
Who are you?

163
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,279
Why are you quarreling with my grandfather?

164
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,680
I'm

165
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:34,319
your grandfather's partner for half his life.

166
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:36,879
People call me Horn of Niu.

167
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:51,639
Hello.

168
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,959
Are you Yunfei?

169
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:53,639
Hello.

170
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,439
We're here to see Academician Niu.

171
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,360
May I ask who you are?

172
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:58,000
He is my father.

173
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,439
My dad was very concerned

174
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,759
when he heard about what happened to Du Juan.

175
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,360
He asked me to come and explain to you.

176
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,480
Over the years,

177
00:08:05,079 --> 00:08:07,839
the models of the fighter jets my dad has been working on

178
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,720
have always been kept at the Aviation School

179
00:08:09,879 --> 00:08:10,920
and maintained by Du Juan.

180
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,279
But this year,

181
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,839
they were found damaged.

182
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:16,480
She came to my father for advice on how to repair them.

183
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,360
These small parts are too old

184
00:08:19,439 --> 00:08:20,360
to be repaired,

185
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,240
so they have to be recast in some old factories.

186
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:25,720
This involves

187
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,519
consultancy fees for retired workers

188
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:30,079
and workshop hourly charges, etc.

189
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,399
So over the years,

190
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,480
Auntie Du spent all her money on this.

191
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,960
Every time, she said

192
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,399
there was no problem with the funds.

193
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,000
We just found out

194
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,799
that she paid for it out of her own pocket.

195
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:45,919
By the way,

196
00:08:48,639 --> 00:08:49,399
this is what my dad said.

197
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,120
We appreciate it.

198
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,039
Listen to me.

199
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:52,879
My dad said

200
00:08:53,039 --> 00:08:54,159
restoring old aircraft models

201
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,440
is the responsibility of every aviation person.

202
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,559
We can't let Du Juan carry it alone.

203
00:08:56,679 --> 00:08:57,320
No, no, no.

204
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:58,399
I absolutely can't take this money.

205
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,039
My mom would be mad at me.

206
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,080
Just take it.

207
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,279
It's a favor.

208
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,120
If you don't,

209
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,559
my dad will scold me.

210
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:05,600
Okay.

211
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,240
How's

212
00:09:10,919 --> 00:09:11,679
Grandpa Niu?

213
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,200
He's old.

214
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,279
He's

215
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,440
in the hospital.

216
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,120
Which hospital?

217
00:09:17,279 --> 00:09:18,200
We'll go visit him.

218
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:19,639
Don't.

219
00:09:19,879 --> 00:09:20,919
He has made it clear

220
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:21,840
that he doesn't want visitors

221
00:09:22,039 --> 00:09:22,799
or gifts.

222
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,600
If anyone asks for the hospital address,

223
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:26,519
just say it's confidential.

224
00:09:27,639 --> 00:09:28,080
By the way,

225
00:09:28,279 --> 00:09:30,039
this is your grandfather's work manual.

226
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,200
My dad has been keeping it.

227
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,799
He said it's time to return it to you.

228
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,600
Alright, I'll be on my way then.

229
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:39,759
Thank you.

230
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:12,080
Why is there a child's handwriting?

231
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:18,639
Little Niu,

232
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:20,240
I think the angle of the tail

233
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:22,559
should be slightly larger.

234
00:10:22,799 --> 00:10:24,559
Wouldn't it be more stable?

235
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,000
Old Du, that's not okay.

236
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,519
A larger angle will increase resistance.

237
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,080
Who will be responsible

238
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,840
if the fuel consumption exceeds the standard?

239
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:33,799
It won't be that big.

240
00:10:34,279 --> 00:10:35,039
What do you mean by that?

241
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,720
Even a little bit more is not allowed.

242
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:38,519
This is my data.

243
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:40,360
Stop arguing.

244
00:10:40,519 --> 00:10:41,600
I've finished writing.

245
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:43,600
What did you write?

246
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,600
Read it to me.

247
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,759
Bamboo in rock

248
00:10:47,799 --> 00:10:50,480
clings to the mountain and never relaxes.

249
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:54,080
Its root is in the broken rock.

250
00:10:54,639 --> 00:10:57,399
It remains strong after all the beatings.

251
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,759
It withstands winds from all directions.

252
00:11:01,399 --> 00:11:02,000
Good.

253
00:11:04,159 --> 00:11:05,360
You're more imposing than your grandpa.

254
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,879
When you grow up,

255
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,519
you'll take over from us

256
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,039
to build big airplanes.

257
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:11,919
Okay?

258
00:11:12,279 --> 00:11:12,679
Okay.

259
00:11:13,159 --> 00:11:13,960
Do you have confidence?

260
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:14,480
Yes.
